**********For Linux (UBUNTU)*********

1.) Run the below command on terminal

curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.11.1/install.sh | bash

2.) Close and Restart the terminal after installing nvm to use properly

3.) The below command will list all the versions

nvm ls-remote

4.) Use the latest and most stable version (It will install node and npm).

nvm install node

5.) For Checking which version you are using for node type the below command

node --version

6.) You can also do

which node

7.) You can also install multiple versions of node, simply repeat the install command with version.

8.) The version which you wants to use, You can run the below command with the version you wants to use

nvm use v7.1.0 (*version number)

9.) For any other help you can type the below command (Help)

nvm -h

**********For Windows*********
1> Download the Node.js source code or a pre-built installer for your platform, and start developing today.
  https://nodejs.org/en/download/
2> Open cmd (run as admin) execute downloaded file using cmd
3> Add path variable C:\Users\webonise\AppData\Roaming\npm some time its automatic added
4> Now repeat ubuntu steps after 5
